xpectations. This research will contribute to the broader field of generative models and have practical implications in various applications, such as content creation, design, and virtual reality.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe challenges include preventing overfitting, maintaining diversity in generated outputs, and optimizing the RLHF pipeline for memory and stability. Naive approaches may lead to suboptimal models that do not align well with human preferences.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has primarily focused on reverse KL divergence, which tends to reduce diversity and cause overfitting. Alternative divergence measures and hybrid approaches have not been extensively explored or integrated into existing frameworks.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed methodology involves developing a hybrid framework that combines RLHF with implicit reward methods, using diverse divergence measures to balance alignment and diversity. The approach will include regularization techniques to prevent overfitting and efficient memory management to optimize the RLHF pipeline. Expected outcomes include improved alignment with human preferences, enhanced output diversity, and reduced memory demands."} {"type": "action_response", "result": "To refine the research proposal, I will address each of the key components systematically. Here is the refined version of the research proposal:\n\n### Refinement of the Research Proposal\n\n#### [Question 1] - What is the problem?\n- **Refined:** How can we enhance the alignment of text-to-image generative models with human preferences while maintaining output diversity and reducing overfitting?\n\n#### [Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?\n- **Refined:** Solving this problem will significantly improve the usability and reliability of text-to-image models, making them more aligned with human expectations. This research will 