# Title: Enhancing Text-to-Image Generation Alignment with Human Preferences Using Diverse Divergence Constraints and Symbolic Reasoning

## Abstract
This research aims to enhance the alignment of text-to-image generative models with human preferences by incorporating diverse divergence constraints and symbolic reasoning. We propose a framework that leverages logistic circuits and the DIGIC framework to improve output diversity and reduce computational demands.

## Introduction
### Background
