Additionally, I have investigated the challenges of inference in discrete graphical models, proposing efficient methods that utilize probabilistic circuits for exact gradient computation. My goal is to create robust machine learning systems that can adapt to real-world complexities while maintaining high performance and reliability. Through my research, I aim to bridge theoretical advancements with practical applications, ultimately contributing to safer and more effective AI systems.

