ements:** Describe the expected improvements in model alignment, computational efficiency, and output diversity.\n   - **Impact on Low-Resource Languages:** Explain how the research will benefit low-resource languages and improve NLP applications for these languages.\n\n5. **Preliminary Results (if available):**\n   - **Pilot Studies:** If any preliminary studies or pilot experiments have been conducted, include the results and how they inform the research proposal.\n\n6. **References:**\n   - **Literature Review:** Include a literature review that supports the research proposal and provides context for the work.\n\n**Example Outline for the Detailed Research Proposal:**\n\n1. **Introduction**\n   - Background and motivation\n   - Research questions and objectives\n\n2. **Literature Review**\n   - Overview of existing work on text-to-image alignment\n   - Discussion of gaps and challenges\n\n3. **Methodology**\n   - Conceptual framework\n   - Adaptation of TransliCo and TransMI\n   - Adaptation of Freeze then Train (FTT)\n   - Datasets and evaluation metrics\n\n4. **Experimental Design**\n   - Detailed description of experiments\n   - Tools and technologies\n   - Timeline\n\n5. **Expected Outcomes**\n   - Performance improvements\n   - Impact on low-resource languages\n\n6. **References**\n   - List of relevant literature\n\nBy developing a detailed research proposal, you can ensure that the research idea is well-structured, feasible, and ready for further development or submission. This will also help in securing funding or support for the project.', 'agent2': 'Given the refined research questions and objectives, the next logical step is to draft a detailed methodology. This will outline the specific algorithms, techniques, and tools that will be used to address the research questions and achieve the objectives. Here’s a structured approach to drafting the methodology section:\n\n### Detailed Methodology\n\n#### 1. **Framework for Diverse Divergence Constraints**\n